This section is to explore the basic user and permisions hardening on kali linux
First of all its very important to know about all the users that are using shell or not and for that i use this command
    cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd
and to know the users that actually using shell or bash i applied this command
    grep "bin/bash" /etc/passwd
this help to distinguish between systen users and real login-capable users like sudo or something like that
A standard user account was created to demonstrate separation of privileges. This account does not have sudo permissions and is intended for non-administrative tasks
the account doesn´t have access to SUDO commands like LS or APT 
this exercise help us to know more about the permissions that an account or a user have in a system
Finally, sensitive system files such as /ETC/SHADOW were reviewed to verify that permissions restrict access to root only proper file permissions are a critical component of Linux security.
